  "description": "Cognitive science is the interdisciplinary study of the mind. Research in Cognitive Science uses behavioral experimentation, computational modeling, and brain imaging to study mental representations and processes. The study of Cognitive Science involves integrating certain areas of focus within Psychology with methods and topics from other disciplines, such as Computer Science, Neuroscience, Linguistics, Philosophy, Anthropology, and Sociology. These are the requirements approved by CCC effective Fall 2024.",
